post.description:
Get any file from a test run dump by specifying the file path.

Examples:
- For results.json: {"file_path": "results.json"}
- For simulator log: {"file_path": "results/espocrm/sim.log"}
- For environment log: {"file_path": "results/espocrm/environments/env_0/env_0.log"}
- For test log: {"file_path": "results/espocrm/environments/env_0/tests/login_base_1/login_base_1.log"}
- For screenshot: {"file_path": "results/espocrm/environments/env_0/tests/login_base_1/screenshots/screenshot.png"}

Generate images using Gemini 2.5 Flash Image model.

The Gemini 2.5 Flash Image model (aka "Nano Banana") supports:
- Text-to-image generation with photorealistic quality
- Blending multiple images into compositions
- Character consistency for storytelling
- Natural language transformations

This endpoint supports both single and batch image generation:
- For a single image: Send batch_params with one item
- For multiple images: Send batch_params with multiple items

Example for single image:
{
    "batch_params": [{
        "prompt": "A hyperrealistic photo of a vintage motorcycle",
        "image_format": "PNG",
        "aspect_ratio": "16:9"
    }]
}

Example for batch:
{
    "batch_params": [
        {"prompt": "A sunset over mountains"},
        {"prompt": "A futuristic city", "aspect_ratio": "3:2"}
    ]
}

Returns:
    GenerateImagesResponse with public S3 asset URLs for each generated image
